The paper presents a system for expanding a seed set of terms into a more complete set of terms that belong to the same semantic class. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as corpus-based methods and iterative workflows. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for selecting and validating the expanded set, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning (ML) techniques such as deep learning (DL) and logistic regression, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as additional likely sub-categories.
